dmugtasimov wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; Stephen,
&gt; 
&gt; this is what I am trying to avoid. I want to have a single TestCase
&gt; that is parameterized to run on any given Algorithm subclass. In your
&gt; example I should create a new TestCase for each Algorighm subclass.
&gt; 
&gt; In practice I have 10 test cases and 10 &quot;Algorithms&quot;. The problem is
&gt; that I don&#39;t want to write and support 100 test classes, bu only 10.

You could try writing a custom suite() method that looks like this:

public static Test suite() {
     TestSuite suite = new TestSuite(&quot;Algorithm tests&quot;);
     suite.add(new AlgorithmTest(new Algorithm1()));
     ...
     suite.add(new AlgorithmTest(new Algorithm99())));
}

where your AlgorithmTest class has a constructor taking the algorithm as 
a parameter, storing it in the fixture, then executing it in the test.
